getClonePtnOrient(25.10)                              getClonePtnOrient(25.10)

Name
       getClonePtnOrient - Retrieves the orientation information of the speci-
       fied partition clone

Syntax
       getClonePtnOrient

       [-help]

       <hinst>

       Retrieves the orientation information of the specified partition clone.
       You can use this command after using the setClonePtnOrient command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief  description of the getClonePtnOrient command.
              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man getClonePtnOrient

       <hinst>
              Specifies the name of the partition clone whose orientation  in-
              formation  has  to be retrieved. This can be an hierarchical in-
              stance name of a partition or an instance name of a black box.

              Note:  The hinst argument should be registered as  a  hinst  and
              not as a string to support DPO usage.

              Data_type: (hinst), required

Example
       The following command retrieves the the orientation information for the
       partition clone TDSP_ARB_C1:

       getClonePtnOrient TDSP_ARB_C1

